title: Looking for advice on best Seattle neighborhood
text:
I am looking to rent a house somewhere in Seattle or a surrounding town. Any advice on neighborhoods/towns that fit the following?:
1. Single family rental home <$2,700 
2. Ideally no more than a 30-45 min bus or bike ride to downtown/south lake union 
3. Safe (feel safe as a woman walking around or taking dog out at night)
4. Preferably has a suburban feel (not a lot of businesses, quiet, near nature, etc) 
5. Beach, lake, or trail access within walking distance 

Thank you!
